CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 20, 1962, pg. 1 reads:"President Kennedy Stumps Area for Democrats - Andrew Hatcher (center) presidential press aide, is shown conferring with reporters as the President arrived, on Friday, at the Greater Pittsburgh Airport."
TitMainTitle: President John F. Kennedy's Press Secretary Andrew Hatcher standing between two reporters in front of Pan American jet clipper Liberty Bell, at airport
